# Generated by `bp build` (Botpress CLI codegen). Regenerated in CI before
# typecheck/build, so it is not committed. See the Botpress integration CI
# workflow's "Generate Botpress typings" step.
.botpress/

# Botpress CLI installs interface/integration packages here via `bp add`.
# This integration adopts the formal `llm` interface via `.extend(llm)`, so
# `bp_modules/llm/` is REQUIRED at build time. `bp add` needs Botpress Cloud
# auth, which CI does not have, so the resolved interface package is VENDORED
# (committed) rather than re-fetched. Do NOT ignore it.

# Built output — produced fresh by `bp build` (Botpress codegen) + `tsup`. NOT
# committed: the integration CI + publish workflows build it from source, the
# `bp deploy` flow builds its own, and the local demo driver
# (deploy/demo/botpress_real/run_botpress_demo.mjs) is self-contained and never
# imports the package. A committed copy could only drift from source — exactly
# the stale-dist bug fixed for the other adapters. Matches flowise/openclaw and
# sdk/typescript (core). botpress is excluded from the dist-drift gate because
# its build needs `bp build` codegen, which the gate's clean checkout can't run.
dist/

# tsup/tsc scratch dirs.
dist-tests/
